README for ripdvd


OVERVIEW
    
ripdvd uses mplayer to copy the titles on a DVD to your hard drive or other 
device. The titles are saved as VOB (MPEG) files which can be played with 
any video player.

Homepage & Instructions:
    http://igurublog.wordpress.com/downloads/script-ripdvd/

Downloads:
    https://github.com/IgnorantGuru/ripdvd
    https://github.com/IgnorantGuru/ripdvd/tree/master/packages

Debian/Ubuntu PPA:
    http://igurublog.wordpress.com/downloads/ppa/
    

INSTALLATION

To install:

    wget https://github.com/IgnorantGuru/ripdvd/raw/master/ripdvd
    sudo install ripdvd /usr/local/bin/ripdvd

To remove:
    
    sudo rm /usr/local/bin/ripdvd


